Kulrick<br>
Zeb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 12:19:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=user.netomia.com/yeishinu/lemming.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee dmg v caster dmg.</span><hr size=1>   Samadhi has found the &quot;insert sarcastic response&quot; button.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umanalow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manalow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 12:39:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee dmg v caster dmg.</span><hr size=1> One wizard cannot drop a mob in ToV.  Agreed.<br>
<br>
Can 5 wizards drop an add in ToV?  I honestly do not know that, as I am not level 60.  I'm not even level 50 with my wizard yet, so I really can't comment on upper end game.<br>
<br>
But if the answer to the above question is yes, then there's usefulness and uniqueness above what a warrior can do.<br>
<br>
5 warriors cannot drop a high level mob because the damage you are refering to is over time.<br>
<br>
One hit with a lammy is going to be around 30 damage.  Factor in tripple attack and duel wield and you get, max without crits, around 120 damage (it's next to impossible to tripple while duel wielding, but you can tripple and double in the same round).  Multiply by an equivilant to how long it takes to cast sunstrike.  Multiply by 5 warriors.  <br>
<br>
My calculations are 821 damage in 7 seconds from 5 level 60 warriors using a cloak of flames, 255 strength, and duel lammys.  That's max damage, not factoring crits, crips, ripostes, parries, dodges, blocks, etc.<br>
<br>
From 5 level 60 wizards in the same 7 seconds (the cast time on Sunstrike) will get maximum of 8075 damage.  This is also not counting interrupts, fizzles, partial resists, total resists, etc.  I wanted to keep it best case scenereo in both cases.<br>
<br>
Again, warriors will outdamage over time.  That goes without further analysis.  The issue I see here is the wizard's role.  I personally don't see wizards as being the biggest damager in the game.  I see wizards as being situationally amazing at damage.  The role was redefined for both wizards and warriors when kunark and velious came out.<br>
<br>
Warriors were given more AC and better weapons because they needed to keep aggro and take huge damage.  Wizards were given bigger spells (sunstrike, ice spear, questionably banes) but were also given other spells such as lures because they were needed.  Lures by themselves show that the class has been somewhat redefined.  Not major damage, but much more likely to connect.<br>
<br>
If wizards were stripped of many large damage spells and given lots of cheap small nukes that could come close to the damage of a warrior, what would be the point of bringing the wizard along at all for?  Ports?  That's what we're trying to avoid.  The fact that wizards CAN do massive damage quickly when needed is one of the defining characteristics of the class.  Take that away and replace it with (essentially) dots or small cheap nukes, and you have a warrior that doesn't use weapons but uses spells instead and one that can't take hits.<br>
<br>
Manalow Gottamed<br>
44th Level Wizard<br>
Bristlebane Server<br>
<br>
Chaotic Conformity<br>
49th Level Warrior<br>
Bristlebane Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 1:41:05 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More ranting!</span><hr size=1> For those of you who say that chaincasting will get us killed, that's a BIG laugh.  Yea, if you chain-cast from the very start of combat, it will get us killed(hell, it's why rangers go down most of the time).  No, the issue is that pre-57, we don't do nearly as much damage as we should.  At 57 and up, you ARE able to pump out good damage, and it's why it's easier to get into groups as you go up in level.  Here's what I noticed as I leveled up from 51 to 60:<br>
<br>
51: Damage output doesn't quite make us desired in groups, but we do a reasonable amount of damage in a group that isn't twinked too badly.  <br>
<br>
52: We get lure, and quickly discover it doesn't do ANYTHING for us except at raids, or when fighting level 60+ mobs, and even then it gets resisted a LOT.  Damage from draught of fire isn't much more, but we get a few extra casts per bar of mana.<br>
<br>
53: We get nothing except our first Jyll's spell, which is great for AoE groups, or going to places like Unrest or Mistmoore.  Draught of fire still doesn't do much more than it did at 51, but we get a few more casts, but still not enough to let us be fully functional in zones like OS where the mobs have a ton of hit points.<br>
<br>
54: Oh, we get a magic based draught, same damage output at 54 and draught of fire at 54, and generally, mobs resist magic more than fire anyway, so it's pretty useless in most zones when fire is available.<br>
<br>
55: We get another lure(fire), and we get the, &quot;Please kill me now&quot; spell commonly known as draught of Jiva.  This spell has so much more agro, that if you chaincast two of these, it agros more than chaincasting 5 draughts of fire. <br>
<br>
56: Like 53, we get another Jyll's, and if you are VERY lucky, you can get a copy of Markar's Discord, but most will probably never see it since it's as rare, or more rare than sunstrike.  So, without Markar's Discord, this level is useless, with that same stupid +5 damage/cast.  BUT, you will start to feel that you can cast a LOT of draughts at 56 on a bar of mana.  It's still not enough to satisfy, but you start to feel like you can burn down a couple of mobs in OS and feel fairly useful as long as you keep C2 up.<br>
<br>
57: This is our biggest jump in damage output, going to 716 cold damage with our new draught.  Suddenly you are able to do a decent amount more per cast, and over a bar of mana, this works well.  OS becomes much easier to deal with since you CAN drop mobs easier in an emergency, but it's useless through most of Velious.<br>
<br>
58 and 59 just give us more casts.  Our flaming sword of crap is actually useful on a FEW mobs that we can't cast on, including on the enraged golem for the wizard epic.  Fetter shows up, and it IS very very useful, like a cross between the old enstill line(holds a long time if you don't attack the mob), and root line for root and nuke.  Fetter CAN break quickly, but when it sticks, it can stick a LONG time, and is good emergency crowd control.<br>
<br>
60 is only useful if you can get the spells, and none of them are available on vendors.  There are also very few mobs that drop the level 60 wizard spells.  So, unless you have 10k+ to spend to buy each spell, you shouldn't expect to get these short of a LOT of really boring camping.<br>
<br>
With epic, or even with manaskin, chaincasting isn't going to get you killed if you wait to cast.  If you focus on stamina, and insist that the cleric give you a symbol buff, you will also be able to do well while chaincasting.  Our epic is a great thing, it lets you chaincast, and help your GROUP more than you may realize if you don't have it yet.  A mob hits you a few times, you either nuke it down, or you concussion the mob and it eventually gets off you.  You just need to play intelligently.<br>
<br>
The wizard class isn't easy to play well, we all know it, and it's why we complain.  I still am upset that the class isn't balanced, but it's NOT that bad at 60, even without the level 60 spells.  But, level 60 isn't the only place that needs to be balanced.  At level 1, 20, 35, 45, 50, and from 51 to 60.  Items need to help our class besides give us more int or stats.<br>
  <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 60 Wizard<br>
Bloodguard of Souls<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
